When a patient no longer requires therapy with KADIAN, taper the dose gradually, by 25% to 50%, every 2 to 4 days, while monitoring for signs and symptoms of withdrawal. If the patient develops these signs or symptoms, raise the dose to the previous level and taper more slowly, either by increasing the interval between decreases, decreasing the amount of change in dose, or both. Do not abruptly discontinue KADIAN [see Warnings and Precautions (
